      "role": "user",
      "content": "But the hope you speak of... it feels like a cruel lie, a mocking whisper in a tomb. Why should I struggle for a flicker of light that only serves to illuminate my misery? The darkness is not an enemy; it is a quiet, welcoming embrace. It is the only thing that doesn't demand anything from me, that doesn't break my heart. Is it truly so wrong to want to simply... leave? To find the stillness that the world refuses to provide?",
